            <div style="margin:40px;font-size:13px;">
                <table>
                    <h2 style="text-align:center;">MEMORANDUM OF UNDERSTANDING</h2>
                    
                    <p style="line-height: 1.5; text-align: justify; font-size: 16px;"><b>This MEMORANDUM OF UNDERSTANDING </b>is executed at Bengaluru on&nbsp;<apex:outputText value="{0,date,dd}{1} Day Of {0,date,MMMM}"><apex:param value="{!NOW()}"/> <apex:param value="{!IF(OR(DAY(DATEVALUE(NOW()))=11,DAY(DATEVALUE(NOW()))=12,DAY(DATEVALUE(NOW()))=13),'th',IF(MOD(DAY(DATEVALUE(NOW())),10)=1,'st',IF(MOD(DAY(DATEVALUE(NOW())),10)=2,'nd',IF(MOD(DAY(DATEVALUE(NOW())),10)=3,'rd','th'))))}"/></apex:outputText> (<apex:outputText value="{0,date,dd.MM.yyyy}"><apex:param value="{!NOW()}"/></apex:outputText>) BY AND BETWEEN </p>
                    
                    <p style="line-height: 1.5; text-align: justify; font-size: 16px;"><b><span style="background-color: none; color: black; padding: 2px 4px;">M/s {!Booking__c.Company_Name__c},</span></b> a Company incorporated under the Companies Act 2013, having its Registered Office at No.750, C’ Block, 1st Main Road, AECS Lay out, Kundalahalli, Bangalore-560037 represented by its authorized signatory Mini Rajavarma- Head- Customer Loyalty. Authorized vide board resolution dated:&nbsp; <apex:outputText value="{0,date,dd-MM-yyyy}"><apex:param value="{!Booking__c.Authorized_Signatory_Resolution_Date__c}"/></apex:outputText>  hereinafter called the FIRST PARTY (which expression shall, wherever the context so admits or requires, mean and include its successors-in-interest, legal representatives, executors, administrators and assigns) on the FIRST PART. </p>
                    
                    <p style="line-height: 1.5; text-align: center; font-size: 16px; font-weight: bold;">AND </p>
                    
                    <p style="line-height: 1.5; text-align: justify; font-size: 16px;">Mr/Ms. {!Booking__c.First_Applicant_Name__c}, Aged about {!Booking__c.Age__c} years, W/o/S/o/C/o. Mr/Ms {!Booking__c.W_o_S_o_C_o__c} (Aadhar No. {!Booking__c.Aadhar_Number__c}), (PAN: {!Booking__c.PAN_Number__c} )</p>
                    
                    <p style="line-height: 1.5; text-align: justify; font-size: 16px;"><apex:repeat value="{!Booking__c.Co_Applicants__r}" var="p"> <div style="text-align:left;">Mr/Ms. {!p.Name}, Aged about {!p.Age__c} years, W/o/S/o/C/o. Mr/Ms {!p.W_o_S_o_C_o__c} (Aadhar No. {!p.Aadhar_Number__c}), (PAN: {!p.PAN_Number__c})</div></apex:repeat></p>
                    
                    <p style="line-height: 1.5; text-align: left; font-size: 16px;">Residing at  {!Booking__c.Address__c}</p>
                    
                    <p style="line-height: 1.5; text-align: justify; font-size: 16px;"> Hereinafter called the SECOND PARTY (which term shall, wherever the context so admits or requires, mean and include his/her/their assigns successors, executors, administrators, heirs &amp; legal representatives) on the <b>SECOND PART.</b></p>
                    
                    <p style="line-height: 1.5; text-align: justify; font-size: 16px;"> WHEREAS <b>FIRST PARTY</b> is sole and absolute owner and at peaceful possession and enjoyment of residentially converted lands bearing&nbsp; 
                        
                        <apex:outputText value="{!
                                                CASE(
                                                Booking__c.Project__c,
                                                'Rhythm of Rain',
                                                'Survey Numbers: 10/4, 10/5, 10/6, 10/7, 11/17, 12/1, 34/3 and 34/4, Katha No.1809, RDPR E- Khatha PID No. 150300402500524218, measuring in all 6 Acre 18 guntas, situated at Samethanahalli Village, Anugondanahalli Hobli, Hosakote Taluk, Bangalore Rural District which is more fully described in the Schedule-A hereunder hereinafter referred to as ',
                                                'Whispering Petals',
                                                'Survey Numbers : 14/2, 75/4, 75/6, 75/7 and 75/9, RDPR E-Katha No.428, PID No. 150300401200521125, in all measuring 6 Acre 07½ guntas, situated at Doddahulluru Village, Kasaba Hobli, Hosakote Taluk, Bangalore Rural District which is more fully described in the Schedule-A hereunder hereinafter referred to as ',
                                                'Euphoria In The East',
                                                'Survey Numbers : 86/1, 86/3, 86/4, 60/2, and 61/4, RDPR E-Katha PID No.150300401000520171, in measuring 8 Acre 23 guntas, situated at Pujena Agrahara Village, Kasaba Hobli, Hosakote Taluk, Bangalore Rural District which is more fully described in the Schedule-A hereunder hereinafter referred to as ',
                                                ''
                                                )
                                                }"/>
                        
                        <b>SCHEDULE A PROPERTY.</b><apex:outputText />
                    </p>                               
                    <div class="page-break"></div>
                     <br/>
                    <p style="line-height: 1.5; text-align: justify; font-size: 16px;">
                        
                        <apex:outputPanel rendered="{!Booking__c.Project__c = 'Rhythm of Rain'}">
                            <b>WHEREAS,</b> the STRR Planning Authority has granted approval to develop the Project vide Commencement Certificate No. STRRPA/TP/CC/188/2024-25, dated 24-12-2024, for construction of Basement, ground plus Fourteen upper Floors of residential apartment building over the Schedule- ''A'' Property.
                        </apex:outputPanel>
                        
                        <apex:outputPanel rendered="{!Booking__c.Project__c = 'Whispering Petals'}">
                            <b>WHEREAS,</b> the STRR Planning Authority has granted approval to develop the Project vide Commencement Certificate No. 26-09-2025, bearing No. HPA/CC/286/2025-26/1737, for construction of Lower Basement, Upper Basement ground plus Nineteen Upper Floors of residential apartment building over the Schedule- ''A'' Property.
                        </apex:outputPanel>
                        
                        <apex:outputPanel rendered="{!Booking__c.Project__c = 'Euphoria In The East'}">
                            <b>WHEREAS,</b> the STRR Planning Authority has granted approval to develop the Project vide Commencement Certificate No. 27-05-2024 bearing No. STRRPA/TP/CC/18/2023-24, for construction of Basement, ground plus Fourteen  upper Floors of residential apartment building over the Schedule-‘A’.
                        </apex:outputPanel>
                        
                    </p>
                    
                    
                    
                    <p style="line-height: 1.5; text-align: justify; font-size: 16px;">WHEREAS the FIRST PARTY has propounded a scheme of ownership units to be built on the Schedule “A” property comprising of residential apartments, (hereinafter called the said scheme) whereunder a persons interested in acquiring a Unit in the building named as<span style="background-color: none; color: black; padding: 2px 4px;"><b>“Sowparnika {!Booking__c.Project__c}”</b></span>being under construction on the Schedule “A” property shall have to acquire a specific undivided right, title and interest in the land covered by the Schedule “A” property by virtue whereof such persons will be granted the right to construct, own and enjoy a specific unit in the said building with all matters of common concern, share, amenities, facilities, liabilities, etc., being looked after in terms of an overall scheme and upon the completion of the said scheme, the land covered by the Schedule “A” property will be owned by all such persons owning the units therein as co-owners.</p>
                    
                    
                    
                    <p style="line-height: 1.5; text-align: justify; font-size: 16px;"> AND WHEREAS pursuant to the above the FIRST PARTY have further offered the purchasers a friendly scheme, wherein the SECOND PARTY on the basis of mutual understanding between the parties, have booked the flat in the proposed residential project. </p>
                    
                    
                    <p style="line-height: 1.5; text-align: justify; font-size: 16px;">The parties have entered into an agreement of sale with certain terms and conditions. Based on the said agreement, the FIRST PARTY will provide all assistance to the SECOND PARTY to apply for a housing loan in the name of SECOND PARTY in order to obtain the housing loan for purchase of the apartment unit The FIRST PARTY herein has offered the reimbursement of Pre-EMI to the SECOND PARTY till the intimation for the Possession. After that the SECOND PARTY shall be responsible for paying the   Pre- EMI/ EMI etc., as per the terms and conditions to the respective bank/ financial institution. In the event the First Party fails to deliver possession of the said flat within the timeline specified under the Agreement of Sale, the First Party shall reimburse the Pre-EMI (Only interest) paid by the Second Party to the financial institution, for the period commencing from the agreed handover date until the date on which the Second Party is formally intimated in writing regarding the readiness of the flat for possession.</p>
                    
                    
                    <p style="line-height: 1.5; text-align: justify; font-size: 16px;">AND WHEREAS in the event of cancellation of the allotment of the apartment unit under this scheme, it is hereby agreed between the parties that the Agreement for Sale and this MOU entered between the parties shall stand cancelled. The FIRST PARTY shall be entitled to forfeit the booking amount of the apartment cost thereafter shall refund the balance advance if any. The SECOND PARTY shall fully co-operate with the First Party to close the SECOND PARTY housing loan with bank or financial institution to the extent of the principal outstanding amount as on the date of settlement by the FIRST PARTY with the bank or financial institution.   </p>
                    
                    <div class="page-break"></div>
                    
                     <br/>
                    
                    <p style="line-height: 1.5; text-align: justify; font-size: 16px;">WHEREAS pursuant to the above scheme and after completely understanding the above scheme and after satisfaction of the title and plan approvals and other details provided by the FIRST PARTY, the SECOND PARTY being interested and decided to book the apartment No. {!Booking__c.Unit_NumberFor__c} in Floor {!Booking__c.Floor__c}<apex:outputText rendered="{!Booking__c.Project__c == 'Rhythm of Rain'}">, Tower {!Booking__c.Block_Number__c}, Building {!Booking__c.Building_No__c}</apex:outputText> <apex:outputText rendered="{!Booking__c.Project__c == 'Whispering Petals'}">, {!Booking__c.Plot__r.Building__c}, {!Booking__c.Block_Name__c} </apex:outputText> having Carpet Area of  {!Booking__c.Carpet_Area__c} square feet,  <apex:outputText rendered="{!Booking__c.Plot__r.Terrace_Area__c != null}">
                        terrace area {!Booking__c.Plot__r.Terrace_Area__c} Sq.ft,
                        </apex:outputText> balcony area of {!Booking__c.Balcony_Area__c} Sq.ft and super built up area of  {!Booking__c.Built_up_area__c} Sq.ft and {!Booking__c.Parking__c} parking together with {!Booking__c.Undivided_Share_Of_Land__c} Sq.ft of undivided share, title and interest in Schedule A property which is more particularly described in Schedule- B (hereinafter referred to as the “Schedule B Property”). </p>
                    
                    
                    <p style="line-height: 1.5; text-align: justify; font-size: 16px;">AND WHEREAS pursuant to the above, the FIRST PARTY and SECOND PARTY have entered into an agreement of sale dated <apex:outputText value="{0,date,d MMMM yyyy}"><apex:param value="{!Booking__c.Sale_Agreement_Date__c}" /></apex:outputText> herein for sale of Schedule B Property. </p>
                    
                    
                    <div style="text-align: left; font-weight: bold; font-size: 16px;">
                        <span style="border-bottom: 1px solid black;">NOW THIS MEMORANDUM OF UNDERSTANDING WITHNESSTH AS FOLLOWS:</span>
                    </div>
                    
                    <p style="line-height: 1.5; text-align: justify; font-size: 16px;">1. The SECOND PARTY has on the date of signing of the MOU paid the amount of Rs. <apex:outputText value="{0, number, ###,###,###,##0}"><apex:param value="{!Booking__c.Total_received_Amount__c}" /></apex:outputText>/-(Rupees {!tillDateReceived} Only) for Schedule “B” &amp; “C” Property. </p>
                    
                    <p style="line-height: 1.5; text-align: justify; font-size: 16px;">2.	The SECOND PARTY hereby agrees to fully co-operate with the FIRST PARTY for applying and obtaining the home loan from the bank or financial institution. Wherein the processing fee shall be borne by the SECOND PARTY.</p>
                    
                    <p style="line-height: 1.5; text-align: justify; font-size: 16px;">3.	The SECOND PARTY also fully agrees to sign all the loan agreements, documents, forms, undertakings, and any other documents required for obtaining home loan and co-operate   fully with the FIRST PARTY or with bank representatives.</p>
                    
                    <p style="line-height: 1.5; text-align: justify; font-size: 16px;">4.	The FIRST PARTY hereby agrees to reimburse the Pre-EMI based on disbursements to the SECOND PARTY till the intimation of Possession. After that SECOND PARTY shall be responsible for payment of interest/ Pre- EMI/ EMI etc., to the respective bank/financial institution. In the event the First Party fails to deliver possession of the said flat within the timeline specified under the Agreement of Sale, the First Party shall reimburse the Pre-EMI (Only interest) paid by the Second Party to the financial institution, for the period commencing from the agreed handover date until the date on which the Second Party is formally intimated in writing regarding the readiness of the flat for possession. The SECOND PARTY also agrees to make the payment of balance consideration towards the flat, registration expenses, stamp duty and miscellaneous charges at the time of registration of the sale deed of the apartment. In this context the term intimation of readiness for possession will mean that the apartment is ready for livable condition and does not include the full completion of all amenities and services.</p>
                    
                    
                    <div class="page-break"></div>
                    
                     <br/>
                    <p style="line-height: 1.5; text-align: justify; font-size: 16px;">5.	 In the event the SECOND PARTY desires to cancel the said allotment of apartment, the SECOND PARTY shall intimate the same in writing to the FIRST PARTY and on receipt of such communication from the SECOND PARTY this MOU, Agreement for Sale shall automatically stands cancelled, and the FIRST PARTY shall repay the housing loan to the respective financial institution as per RERA rules for which Second Party shall fully cooperate with the FIRST PARTY.</p>

                    <div style="text-align: center; font-weight: bold; font-size: 16px;">
                        
                        <span style="border-bottom: 1px solid black;">SCHEDULE “A” PROPERTY</span>
                    </div>            
                    
                    <p style="line-height: 1.5; text-align: justify; font-size: 16px;">
                        
                        <apex:outputPanel rendered="{!Booking__c.Project__c = 'Rhythm of Rain'}">
                            All that piece and parcel of residential converted lands bearing (i) Sy No-10/4 (Old Sy No.10/1) measuring 37 guntas (converted vide Official Memorandum No:492757, dated 25-04-2023), (ii) Sy No- 10/5 (Old Sy No.10/4) measuring 0-10 guntas (converted vide Official Memorandum No:492762, dated 25-04-2023) (iii) Sy No-10/6 (Old Sy No.10/4) measuring 0-10 guntas (converted vide Official Memorandum No:492760, dated 25-04-2023) (iv) Sy No-10/7 (Old Sy No.10/4) measuring 0-37 guntas (converted vide Official Memorandum No:492758, dated 25-04-2023) (v) Sy No-11/17 measuring (Old Sy No.11/1B) 0-14 guntas (converted vide Official Memorandum No:492754, dated 25-04-2023) (vi) Sy No- 12/1 measuring 1 Acre 30 guntas (converted vide Official Memorandum No:492767 , dated 25-04-2023) (vii) Sy No-34/3 (Old Sy No.34) measuring 1 Acre (converted vide Official Memorandum No:492755, dated 25-04-2023) (viii) Sy No- 34/4 (Old Sy No.34) measuring 1 Acre (converted vide Official Memorandum No:492756, dated 25-04-2023), Katha No.1809, RDPR PID No. 150300402500524218, measuring in all 6 Acre 18 guntas, situated at Samethanahalli Village, Anugondanahalli Hobli, Hosakote Taluk, Bangalore Rural District, and commonly bounded on that: 
                        </apex:outputPanel>
                        
